        <h3>JobTread — Best job-cost-linked time tracking</h3>
        <p>JobTread's time tracking is tightly integrated with its job costing system. Labor hours logged through the mobile app become actual labor costs on the job in real time. The system supports cost codes, which means you can track time by trade phase and see exactly where your labor is going on each project.</p>

        <div class="cta-box">
          <p><strong>JobTread's time tracking updates job costing in real time — know your labor margin on every job.</strong></p>
          <a href="https://www.jobtread.com" rel="nofollow sponsored" class="btn btn-outline">Try JobTread</a>
        </div>

        <h3>Raken — Best for daily report + time card combo</h3>
        <p>Raken combines daily reports with time tracking in a mobile-first format that field crews actually complete. Workers log time while completing their daily report — two tasks in one workflow. For GCs who need both consistent daily documentation and accurate labor hours, Raken's approach is efficient.</p>

        <h3>Dedicated time tracking tools</h3>
        <p>For contractors who need time tracking but don't need a full construction management platform, dedicated tools like Clockify, TSheets (now QuickBooks Time), or Busybusy offer GPS-verified mobile time tracking with payroll integration at lower price points. These can be effective supplements if your primary construction software lacks strong time tracking.</p>

        <h2>The job costing connection</h2>
        <p>Time tracking is only valuable if the hours get attributed correctly to specific jobs and cost categories. A platform where workers clock in "on a job" but all hours pool into one bucket doesn't give you job costing data — it just gives you total hours. Make sure your time tracking solution supports cost code assignment so field labor becomes actionable job cost data.</p>

